</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="about-hero">
  <div class="about-hero-left">
    <span class="page-tag">✦ Start Here</span>
    <h1 class="about-headline">Not just reviews.<br><em>Directions.</em></h1>
    <p class="about-sub">Chirpbase Reads exists for the avid reader and the curious beginner alike — anyone who's ever stared at a shelf and thought, "but where do I even start?"</p>
  </div>
  <div class="about-hero-right">
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="The Chirpbase">
    <p class="about-hero-tagline">"A place where books are not just read, but experienced, remembered, and emotionally processed."</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WHAT IS THIS -->
<div class="content-section">
  <div class="content-section-label">
    <span class="section-label-text">What is this</span>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section-body">
    <h2>A reading guide that actually feels human.</h2>
    <p>Chirpbase Reads is not your average book review platform. There are no dry academic breakdowns here, no spoiler-heavy plot summaries, and absolutely no pretending books are more complicated than they need to be.</p>
    <p>This is a space built on the idea that the best reason to recommend a book isn't its Goodreads score — it's <span class="highlight">how it made you feel</span>. Whether it wrecked you quietly, made you laugh at yourself, or gave you the words for something you'd been carrying around for years.</p>
    <p>If you've been eyeing a particular book but you're skeptical, if you want a nudge in the right direction, or if you just want someone with actual taste to point you somewhere new — you're in the right place.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WHO IS BEHIND THIS -->
<div class="content-section">
  <div class="content-section-label">
    <span class="section-label-text">Who's behind this</span>
  </div>
  <div class="content-section-body">
    <h2>A multipotentialite who made peace with her range.</h2>
    <p>Chirpbase Reads lives under <span class="highlight">The Chirpbase</span> — a creative media brand covering culture, music, relationships, mental health, and lifestyle commentary. Think of it as the reading arm of a much larger conversation.</p>
    <p>The person behind it? A multipotentialite who has fully embraced her versatility as a superpower. Funny, curious, perpetually challenging herself, and always exploring new ideas — which is probably why the shelves here go from Chimamanda to dark romance with zero apology.</p>
    <p>The reviews are honest. The verdicts are personal. And the recommendations come from someone who actually read the book and has feelings about it.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WHAT YOU'LL FIND -->
<section>
  <div style="padding: 2.5rem 4rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 400;">What you'll find here</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="features-grid">
    <div class="feature-item">
      <span class="feature-emoji">📖</span>
      <h3 class="feature-title">Honest Reviews</h3>
      <p class="feature-desc">Every book broken down by vibe, emotional impact, who it's for, and a Chirpbase Verdict — our signature sign-off on whether it's worth your time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-item">
      <span class="feature-emoji">🗂️</span>
      <h3 class="feature-title">Curated Shelves</h3>
      <p class="feature-desc">Books organised by feeling, not just genre. Soft Destruction. Grief & Loss. Books for Your 20s. Fiction That Lingers. Find exactly what you need right now.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-item">
      <span class="feature-emoji">🔗</span>
      <h3 class="feature-title">Where to Get Them</h3>
      <p class="feature-desc">We don't just tell you what to read — we point you to where you can actually get it. Links, vendors, and sources so nothing stays out of reach.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- START HERE -->
<div class="start-here">
  <div class="start-here-left">
    <h2>Not sure where to begin?</h2>
    <p>Here are a few good entry points depending on where you are right now — emotionally, mentally, or just in terms of what kind of read you're looking for.</p>
    <div class="start-links">
      <a href="index.html" class="start-link-item">
